      "span_text": "In his classic work An Economic Theory of Democracy, Anthony  suggests that, \"since the odds are that no election will be close enough to render decisive the vote of any one person, or the votes of all those he can persuade to agree with him, the rational course of action for most citizens is to remain politically uninformed\"."
